      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sweet shortcrust, blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}} and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Bind with the yolk of the first {{eggs}} and the {{water}}. Wrap and chill an hour. Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Roll thinly, line a 23 cm tart tin, trim flush with the rim, and prick the base. Blind-bake with beans for 15 minutes; remove paper and beans and bake another 8 minutes until pale gold all over. Brush the warm pastry with the reserved egg white to seal.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Lemon filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drop the oven to 140°C fan. Whisk the zest of 3 {{lemon}} with the {{caster-sugar}} until the zest releases its oils into the sugar. Add the juice of all 5 {{lemon}}, the five beaten {{eggs}} and the {{double-cream}}. Whisk gently until smooth. Pass through a fine sieve to remove zest and any stringy bits.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Low set, 35 minutes",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp99bux400004gv4l7tgsz23"
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Set the pastry shell on a baking tray in the oven (this stops the filling spilling on the way in). Pour the filling in to the brim. Bake at 140°C fan for 30 to 35 minutes; the edges should be set, the centre should still wobble slightly. Cool fully to room temperature; the residual heat finishes the set.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
